# Fork Language Rules

## Language Tool Table (Fork Rows)
- These rows extend the Language tool table in `engineering.prompt`. Procure these tools from the registry or release listed per row, not from `github.com/unclebob/...` repositories.
- JavaScript/TypeScript: install with npm or Bun; mutation `mutate4js` (npm), CRAP `@gabadi/crap4js` (npm only, never from GitHub), DRY `drywall`.
- Python: install with uv or pip; mutation `mutate4py` (PyPI), CRAP `crap4py` (PyPI), DRY `drywall`.
- drywall: download the platform binary from the latest `github.com/gabadi/drywall` release (`drywall-linux-x86_64`, `drywall-macos-aarch64`, or `drywall-macos-x86_64`), `chmod +x`, place on PATH. Fallback: `cargo install --git https://github.com/gabadi/drywall`.

## Branch Coverage
- Always enable branch coverage for these rows; the CRAP and mutation tools require LCOV BRDA records.
- Python: `pytest --cov --cov-branch --cov-report=lcov:lcov.info` (or `branch = True` in the coverage config).
- JavaScript/TypeScript: enable the test runner's `lcov` coverage reporter (writes `coverage/lcov.info`).
- Pass the LCOV file explicitly: `crap4py src/ --lcov lcov.info`; `mutate4py path/to/file.py --lcov lcov.info` or `--cov-cmd`; `mutate4js path/to/file.ts --test-command "<cmd>" --cov-cmd "<coverage cmd>"`. `crap4js` reads `coverage/lcov.info` by default.
